          <LEXSenses>
            <LEXSense LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="2021-10-19 11:21:15" LastEditedBy="">
              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>to cut, by means of a sharp-edged instrument (for example, knife, sword, or ax)</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>to cut</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>In a number of languages important distinctions are made for various types of cutting. For example, terms referring to the cutting of flesh may be different from those involving wood or stone. Similarly, important distinctions may be made as to whether there is simply an incision by cutting or whether a particular object is cut in two or cut off.</Comments>
            </LEXSense>
